                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/106</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Siam</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AFD1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Arnold</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-13T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your August 7, 10 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d594fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1917Supp01v01#pg_454">Supplement 1, p. 454</ref>.</note>
                    Telegraph exact status of situation. American Government desires to be
                    considered in any apportionment of these steamers and you will so notify Siamese
                    Government. Department understands that it is proposed to allot 35 per cent to
                    the British, a similar amount to the French, and 30 per cent to the Japanese,
                    with the understanding that the latter will utilize the tonnage or its
                    equivalent in relieving the war needs of the Allies, to which restriction the
                    Japanese object. American Government especially anxious to share in the
                    distribution of this tonnage and you will keep Department informed of any
                    developments that may give this Government opportunity to participate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
